her", "w": "69077"}]}, {"id": "17724", "date": "1972-07-02", "label": "Newport Jazz Festival: Count Basie and His Orchestra with Benny Carter and The Swing Masters: Swing Lives", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["vocalist"], "works": [{"t": "I Want a Little Girl", "c": "Murray Mencher", "w": "69077"}]}, {"id": "16567", "date": "1976-07-04", "label": "Newport Jazz Festival: The Ellington Saga, Part IV", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["vocalist"], "works": [{"t": "Don't Get Around Much Anymore", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "3924"}, {"t": "Do Nothing Till You Hear From Me", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "3244"}]}, {"id": "702", "date": "1992-05-19", "label": "Cavalcade of Stars to Benefit the Shield Institute", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["vocalist"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}], "works_created": [], "quotes": [], "about_quotes": [{"speaker": "Roland Hanna", "relation": "played with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "I went to work with Al Hibbler. And Al Hibbler and I were in Miami, Florida, playing in a hotel/bar type place that had a restaurant.", "doc_title": "Roland Hanna interviewed by Monk Rowe, Scottsdale, Arizona, April 15, 2000", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/roland-hanna-interviewed-monk-rowe-scottsdale-arizona-april-15-2000"}, {"speaker": "John Malachi", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "he would like for me to travel with him as his pianist... I worked with him... we did a theatre tour over there", "doc_title": "68089_John Malachi oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/68089/"}, {"speaker": "Big Nick Nicholas", "relation": "friend of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "Al Hibbler, I really appreciate him calling me and he's always been a real close friend throughout the years.", "doc_title": "67619_Big Nick Nicholas oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/67619/"}, {"speaker": "Jay Cee Johnson", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "Some of J. C.'s songs were recorded by the following people: ... Al Hibbler ...", "doc_title": "68252_Jay Cee", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/68252/"}, {"speaker": "Don Albert", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "And he want to join my band and he had sung some numbers with me... Later years he came to San Antonio, I used him at my nightclub", "doc_title": "Don Albert Interview, 1972-09-18", "collection": "tulane", "url": "https://library.search.tulane.edu/permalink/01TUL_INST/4h6sc4/alma9945592969906326"}, {"speaker": "Trummy Young", "relation": "has met", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "But I met those guys, I met Al Hibbler down in San Antonio, Texas. And then I also met Al in Little Rock, Arkansas.", "doc_title": "52300_Trummy Young oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/52300/"}]}